From: Hadron Port <hadron@localhost>
Date: 2026-01-01
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] lavapipe: disable LLVM JIT for Phase 1 (interpreter fallback)

LLVM cross-compilation for Hadron is out of scope for Phase 1.
Mesa lavapipe has a non-JIT fallback (TGSI interpreter) that is
significantly slower but requires no LLVM. This patch forces the
non-JIT path when __hadron__ is defined. Phase 2 can re-enable JIT
once LLVM is available as a static library in the sysroot.

diff --git a/src/gallium/drivers/llvmpipe/lp_screen.c b/src/gallium/drivers/llvmpipe/lp_screen.c
--- a/src/gallium/drivers/llvmpipe/lp_screen.c
+++ b/src/gallium/drivers/llvmpipe/lp_screen.c
@@ -68,6 +68,12 @@
 lp_screen_create(struct pipe_screen_config *config)
 {
+#if DETECT_OS_HADRON && !defined(HADRON_ENABLE_LLVM_JIT)
+   /* Force non-JIT path: LLVM is not yet available as a Hadron sysroot lib. */
+   lp_set_no_jit(true);
+   fprintf(stderr, "[lavapipe] LLVM JIT disabled on Hadron (Phase 1). "
+                   "Performance will be reduced.\n");
+#endif
+
    /* ... existing screen creation unchanged ... */
 }
